SYNOPSIS
========
   mixed include_file(string file, string compiled_file, int sys_include)

DESCRIPTION
===========
   Generate the pathname of an included file.

   Arguments:

      previous_object()
         The object causing the compile.

      file
         The name given in the #include directive.

      compiled_file
         The object file which is just compiled. (compat: name given
         withoutleading "/")

      sys_include
         TRUE for #include <> directives.

   Result:

      `0`
         use the normal include filename generation (""-includes are used
         asthey are, <>-includes are handled according to H_INCLUDE_DIRS).

      `<path>`
         the full absolute pathname of the file to include, without
         parentdirparts ("/../"). Leading slashes ("/") may be omitted.

      else
         The include directive is not legal.

   If the function does not generate a valid pathname, the driver will nexttry
   to resolve the include using the H_INCLUDE_DIRS hook.
